The House of Representatives just voted decisively to block President Trump’s national emergency declaration to fund his long-promised southern border wall.
“It’s clear there’s no emergency at the border.”Apart from the national emergency declaration potentially being a Constitutional issue, other Democrats have raised concerns there’s racist intent behind it.
The national emergency declaration is also facing intense opposition on other fronts.
And on Monday, 59 former national security advisers wrote a bipartisan letter to say there isn’t a national emergency on the border.
